# Generic Core Standards

Read [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) first. Obey [generic-binding-flow](generic-binding-flow.mdc) — no shortcuts.

## Git flow

- **Branch first** — before any feature/fix code, `git checkout -b feature/...` or `fix/...` from `main`
- Never commit directly to `main`
- One logical change per PR
- Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, ...)

## Validation (automatic)

After `bash scripts/bootstrap.sh`, git hooks run **`bash scripts/validate.sh`** (same as CI). Do not skip hooks. Cursor hook `enforce-git-flow.sh` also blocks `--no-verify` and commits on `main`.

## Documentation

Update in the same PR as code:

- `CHANGELOG.md` → `[Unreleased]` for behaviour changes
- `docs/INDEX.md` when adding docs
- `AGENTS.md` when agent workflow changes

## Versioning

Primary: **release-please** on merge to `main`. Do not hand-edit versions in normal flow.
Offline fallback only: `bash scripts/bump-version.sh`.

## Language

**English only** in the repository — code, comments, docs, commits.
See `.agents/skills/generic-language/SKILL.md`.

## Secrets

Never commit secrets. Use `.env` (gitignored) and `.env.example`.

## Token efficiency

Use `caveman` / `cavecrew` when the user asks for terse responses or long sessions.
